  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/fea-predicts-compression-bending-noncannulated",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "FEA accurately predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending behavior of non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct",
      "description": "The FEA modeling framework, implemented across three independent analyst teams (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes), accurately predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading. Supporting evidence includes mesh convergence studies demonstrating discretization errors below 1.5%, material property characterization from coupon testing of Ti-6Al-4V rod stock, and inter-laboratory experimental repeatability data from two independent test facilities. All three quantities of interest fall within the pre-established 10% acceptance bound and yield E/uval ratios below 1.96, consistent with ASME V&V 40 requirements for medium model risk at medium decision consequence. The ensemble approach further reduces the influence of any single analyst's modeling choices, strengthening confidence in the prediction. This claim underpins the regulatory submission asserting that bench testing alone is sufficient to characterize construct performance without additional clinical studies."
    }
  ],
  "wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4040902",
