      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions must be solved to confirm correct implementation of governing equations.",
      "rationale": "Beam bending and contact patch benchmark cases solved against Hertzian and Euler-Bernoulli analytical solutions. Maximum deviation 0.8%. Code verification complete across all relevant element types (SOLID186, CONTA174)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change less than 2% between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on screw-rod interface region. Stiffness QoI changed 1.4% between medium and fine mesh; yield force changed 0.9%. Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI < 1.5% for all QoIs. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals must converge below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error below 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) employed for all load steps. Force residuals converged to 1e-8. Energy balance monitored; maximum error 0.04% across all 11 construct simulations. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup; documented checklist covering boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions.",
      "rationale": "Three independent analyst teams built models from a common specification. Cross-team comparison of boundary condition definitions, contact pair assignments, and material property inputs performed. Discrepancies resolved by consensus. Formal review checklist completed and archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection justified by material characterization data; contact formulation appropriate for screw-rod interface physics.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model for Ti-6Al-4V calibrated against coupon tensile test data (n=6 specimens). Augmented Lagrange contact formulation selected for screw-rod interface; frictional coefficient 0.2 based on tribology literature. Model form appropriate for quasi-static compression-bending regime."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometry, and boundary conditions must be traceable to measured data or published standards with uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus 114 GPa, yield strength 880 MPa, tangent modulus 1.2 GPa derived from coupon testing. Geometry from manufacturer CAD files verified against CMM measurements (max deviation 0.03 mm). Uncertainty propagation via Monte Carlo (n=1000 samples) quantified combined input uncertainty at 3.1% for stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental constructs must be production-representative; lot traceability and dimensional inspection documented for N>=10 specimens.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-lot components (lot traceability documented). Pre-test CMM inspection confirmed all screw and rod dimensions within drawing tolerances. Constructs distributed across two independent laboratories (n=6 and n=5) to assess inter-laboratory variability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of loading scenarios relevant to the COU, including at least two load levels and two loading rates.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load rate (5 mm/min) and single environmental condition (ambient, dry). ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standard condition; no variation in loading rate or environment was explored. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3 — this factor is the identified gap in the credibility assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to experimental conditions; any differences must be assessed for impact on QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Material properties, geometry, boundary conditions, and loading protocol in FEA replicate experimental setup. Fixture compliance measured experimentally and incorporated into model boundary conditions. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that residual differences in grip compliance (<2 N/mm) alter stiffness QoI by less than 0.5%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E/uval) must be computed for all QoIs; acceptance threshold pre-specified before unblinding.",
      "rationale": "E/uval metric computed for all three QoIs following ASME V&V 40 Eq. 6-1. Pre-specified acceptance threshold E/uval < 1.96 documented in validation plan prior to experimental unblinding. All three QoIs satisfy criterion: stiffness E/uval=0.41, yield force E/uval=0.20, force at 40 mm E/uval=0.33. Percentage differences all below 3%, well within 10% bound."
    },
    {
